{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d924538-fb23-4712-9232-e8ba66a4e5ab","content":"Use MAUI's `#if` platform directives in `MauiProgram.cs` to conditionally register each implementation:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.iOSNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\nEach implementation lives under `Platforms/<target>/` and is only compiled for its platform. This ensures no missing-type errors at build time.\n\n**Key points:**\n- The symbols `ANDROID`, `IOS`, `WINDOWS` are defined automatically by the MAUI SDK per target framework.\n- Place each implementation in its respective `Platforms/` folder so the default `.csproj` glob rules scope it to the right platform.\n- Inject `INotificationService` in your shared code via constructor injection as usual.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"078203b6-9313-438d-9343-a098f7b4edec","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` interface in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":375,"requestId":"F3C7:20AC41:1F171D2:22F3830:69E81BAA"},"id":"d9060366-ee99-4609-8454-8b515980dcd3","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:52:03.382Z","parentId":"aa53050e-3e4e-4513-9899-1a901f36a490"}
